<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: EricssonNMSCIM
==========================================================================================================================
This element is the root element in the topology.

Attribute: CIMVERSION
Simply use "2.4". It is kept in the DTD due to backward compatibility reasons. The content of this element is not used.

Attribute: DTDVERSION
Simply use "1.0". It is kept in the DTD due to backward compatibility reasons. The content of this element is not used.
==========================================================================================================================
-->
<!ELEMENT EricssonNMSCIM (OPERATION)>
<!ATTLIST EricssonNMSCIM
	CIMVERSION CDATA #IMPLIED
	DTDVERSION CDATA #IMPLIED
>
<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: OPERATION
==========================================================================================================================
This element is kept for backward compatibility reasons.

Attribute: TYPE:
Simply use "purge". It is kept in the DTD due to backward compatibility reasons. The content of this element is actually not used.

Attribute: PROTOCOLVERSION
Simply use "1.0".
==========================================================================================================================
-->
<!ELEMENT OPERATION (EricssonNMS)>
<!ATTLIST OPERATION
	PROTOCOLVERSION CDATA #REQUIRED
	TYPE (purge | modify | add | delete) #IMPLIED
>
<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: EricssonNMS
==========================================================================================================================
This element is kept for backward compatibility reasons.

Attribute: (No attributes!)
-->
<!ELEMENT EricssonNMS (EriNMSSubNW)>
<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: EriNMSSubNW
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent a sub network, but is actually not used anymore. It is kept for backward compatibility reasons.

Attribute: cimname
This is the name of the sub network. Simply use "Service Network".
-->
<!ELEMENT EriNMSSubNW (SNOSNE*)>
<!ATTLIST EriNMSSubNW
	cimname CDATA #REQUIRED
>
<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: SNOSNE
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent an object in the system topology, for example subsystem, component or function.

Attribute cimname:
The name of the object. Use an abbreviation, for example EMA for the Ericsson 
Multi Activation. The cimName must be unique for a system.

Attribute cimdescription:
This is a description of the object.

Attribute cimcaption:
The full name of the object. For example Ericsson Multi Activation for EMA.

Attribute cimotheridentifyinginfo:
This is the resource identity of an alarming resource using the SNF SNMP protocol. 
The resource identity must start with 1, 2 or 3, is in format x.x.x... and 
have a minimum value length of 2 (for example 1.4.28). This is used for mapping 
of alarms to objects. This attribute is optional for all systems not using the 
SNF SNMP protocol.

Attribute cimidentifyingdescription:
This is a description of the resource identity in 'cimotheridentifyinginfo'.

Attribute syscontact:
This is the name of the person responsible for a system.

Attribute syslocation:
This is the geographical location of a system.

Attribute snoshostip:
This is the IP address of the host where the System/Component resides.

Attribute snosversion:
This is the version of the System/Component.

Attribute snoshostname:
This is the hostname of the host where the System/Component resides.

Attribute snossnmpcommunity:
This is the SNMP community string to use when connecting to the SNMP agent on 
the host.

Attribute snossnmpport:
This is the SNMP port to use when connecting to the SNMP agent on the host.

Attribute snosalarmmoi:
The alarmManagedObjectInstance for a system sending alarms according to the 
ERICSSON-ALARM-IRP-MIB. It is used to identify an alarming resource in a 
system supporting the ERICSSON-ALARM-IRP-MIB. The combination of SNOSHostIP 
and SNOSAlarmMOI must be unique. Note: This optional attribute is mandatory 
when using the ERICSSON-ALARM-IRP-MIB, for example when SNMS is integrated with OSS-RC FM.

Attribute snosprotocoltype:
The type of SNMP protocol used by the system. Valid values are SNF, IRP, MST, SNMP, TXF.

Attribute snostype:
The type of system. Used for example by the MST solution to find the correct 
trap translations. Examples: MMC, MIEP, SDP(ESA) or SunMC. This attribute 
is required when snosprotocoltype is set to MST. Also used by the TXF interface to 
find the correct TXF translate map.
-->

<!ELEMENT SNOSNE (SNOSNE | SNOSOP | SnmpCounterSet | IrpXmlCounterSet | RemoteFileFetch)* >
<!ATTLIST SNOSNE
	cimname CDATA #REQUIRED
	cimdescription CDATA #IMPLIED
	cimcaption CDATA #IMPLIED
	cimotheridentifyinginfo CDATA #IMPLIED
	cimidentifyingdescription CDATA #IMPLIED
	syscontact CDATA #IMPLIED
	syslocation CDATA #IMPLIED
	snoshostip CDATA #REQUIRED
	snosbackupip CDATA #IMPLIED
	snosversion CDATA #IMPLIED
	snoshostname CDATA #IMPLIED
	snossnmpcommunity CDATA #IMPLIED
	snossnmpport CDATA #IMPLIED
	snosalarmmoi CDATA #IMPLIED
	snosprotocoltype (SNF | IRP | MST | SNMP | TXF | MVMALARM) #IMPLIED
	snostype CDATA #REQUIRED
>

<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: SnmpCounterSet
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent an SNMP based PM counter set.
-->
<!ELEMENT SnmpCounterSet EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST SnmpCounterSet
	fileName CDATA #REQUIRED
	ROP ( 1 | 5 | 15 | 60 ) #REQUIRED
>

<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: IrpXmlCounterSet
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent an IRP XML based PM counter set.
-->
<!ELEMENT IrpXmlCounterSet EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST IrpXmlCounterSet
	fileName CDATA #REQUIRED
	regExp CDATA #REQUIRED
	ROP ( 1 | 5 | 15 | 60 ) #REQUIRED
>


<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: RemoteFileFetch
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent an Remote File Fetch.
-->
<!ELEMENT RemoteFileFetch (RemoteFileCounterSet+)>
<!ATTLIST RemoteFileFetch
	pluginDir CDATA #REQUIRED
	ROP ( 5 | 15 | 60 | 120 | 1440) #REQUIRED
	ProtocolType ( SFTP ) #REQUIRED
	Offset CDATA #IMPLIED
>


<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: RemoteFileCounterSet
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent an Remote file based PM counter set.
-->
<!ELEMENT RemoteFileCounterSet EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST RemoteFileCounterSet
	fileName CDATA #IMPLIED
	regExp CDATA #IMPLIED
 >


<!--
==========================================================================================================================
Element: SNOSOP
==========================================================================================================================
This element represent an operation possible to run on the object in the topology, 
for example subsystem, component or function.

A number of operations (start, stop, restart, status, config) may be supported by a 
system/component. If a system/component supports any of these operations, the access 
to these operations shall be stored in the O&M data model.

The operation config gives the possibility to store the access to a number of 
configuration tools for a system/component in the O&M data model.

Attribute cimname:
The name of the operation. If the operation config is chosen, then cimName 
should contain the name of the configuration tool.

Attribute cimdescription:
This is a description of the object.

Attribute cimcaption:
The full name of the object. For example Ericsson Multi Activation for EMA.

Attribute snosopname:
Indicates an operation on a system/component. Type & range: start, stop, restart, 
status, enableautostart,

disableautostart, lock, unlock, shutdown, state, config

Attribute snosoptype:
Indicates how to execute the chosen operation.

Attribute snosopargument:
Indicates the command to execute the chosen operation, for example a web link 
or a CLI command string.

Attribute snosopuser:
Indicates the user to execute the chosen operation. If this attribute is 
left out, user root is used.
-->
<!ELEMENT SNOSOP EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST SNOSOP
	cimname CDATA #REQUIRED
	cimdescription CDATA #IMPLIED
	cimcaption CDATA #IMPLIED
	snosopname (start | stop | restart | status | enableautostart | disableautostart | lock | unlock | shutdown | state | config) #REQUIRED
	snosoptype (URL | script) #REQUIRED
	snosopargument CDATA #REQUIRED
	snosopuser CDATA #IMPLIED
>
